    <h1>
        Message from Director of Schools
    </h1>
    <p>
        </p>
<p><span style="font-size:large;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Governor Bill Lee recommended today that all Tennessee schools should remain closed for the remainder of the school year.  West Carroll Special School District will comply with our Governor  and remain closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020  school year.  There are many decisions to be made and even more questions to be answered.  We will soon be posting answers to those questions that you may have.  At this time, we are waiting for more guidance from the Tennessee Department of Education concerning the logistics of closing schools.  Please continue to FREQUENTLY check our district website and Facebook page for updates and additional information.  We were saddened by today's announcement, but we do understand that the safety of our students, faculty, and staff is the number one concern.  Our faculty and staff miss our students and are anxiously waiting for the start of next school year.  Please feel free to email me if you have any questions.     </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:large;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Dexter Williams </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:large;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Director of Schools  West Carroll Special School District  </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:large;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">dexter.williams@wcssd.org</span></p>
    
